  "text": "Other authors have proposed enforcement architectures to control access to data objects distributed to remote systems [CITATION_1] . Such architectures control how outsourced applications can access outsourced objects at runtime, assuming that these applications are trusted after verifying their load-time integrity. As we discussed before, behavior compliance control goes well beyond such load-time based measures.",
